race.comment: Much like the Crawford Stakes many here are resuming and aiming for richer races into the summer. MAGNIFICENT ANDY (1) is one run up on most of them and returned with a big win to claim the million-dollar Golden Saddle at Kalgoorlie. Fitter again and will be tough to beat. WATCH ME ROCK (7) is a progressive type who won three on the trot at the end of last campaign and will be going for the top level this campaign. Has never missed the frame fresh though including two wins and Pike stays aboard. BONJOY (10) is another talent resuming. Has a superb strike-rate at Ascot and will be hard to hold out late. BUCKETS RIDGE (8) resumes and may want a little further but presents on the back of two trials. Has claims on best form. ZIPAWAY (3) was a fast finishing fourth fresh and is a second-up winner. Will be winding up late.
